@startuml
title Measurement Publication and Frontend Read

participant "Hardware Provider" as provider
database "Channel Measurement Buffer" as buffer
participant "VC Worker" as worker
database "Canonical Channel State" as state
participant "Register Catalog" as catalog
participant "Frontend" as frontend

provider -> buffer : publish voltage/current + timestamp
provider -> worker : wake semaphore
worker -> buffer : synchronized evidence read
worker -> state : calibrate, protect, ramp, recover

frontend -> catalog : read measurement Semantic Register
catalog -> state : VC owner lock + scalar read
state --> catalog : calibrated value
catalog --> frontend : typed value

note over frontend,state
No dense snapshot mirror and no blocking hardware acquisition.
end note
@enduml
